Life is like a roller coaster, full of excitement, doubt, uncertainty, and fun. From one moment to another you feel that you go up, you are at the top, but unconsciously you let yourself be carried away (which is normal) until you finish in the deepest, but there you take the inertia to go back up, but suddenly there is an unexpected turn and you take a ride ... we scream on the roller coaster for our emotional spikes. This is life, it goes like a roller coaster which is why we have emotional peaks. As a roller coaster begins also ends, the important thing is to have enjoyed it, and to have enjoyed the journey. Does a roller coaster with no ups, no downs and no turns generate any emotion? Right not? We want it to be fun and to generate adrenaline, we want something that moves us everywhere. That does seem to be an interesting roller coaster to experience, right? Well that's what life is about. Life is like a roller coaster and that's what makes it interesting. SantiagoCandela 14-Mar-21 07:41 AM
Man I can relate to Kelly a lot, I had it too. So let me tell u what you should do in this case (although I didn’t fix myself with it, but I think is one of the best ways). First, Panic attacks usually occurs because our mind is focusing in the future, but in a bad circumstances. Like we imagine something bad going to happen to us and we get worried of something we can’t control (most of the time). So we get afraid, and our mind is already acting like if that is happening because she can’t distinguish of “what’s now”. Is about visualizing and our imagination, all those things, panic attacks, afraid or whatever, is a mental monster we create and we are the only one that can control that and get rid of it. Please, the best you can do is to FOCUS on RIGHT NOW, HERE, present. Stay PRESENT. To do that, focus on your breath, or your hand, watch your hand, touch it, feel it, or anything, it could be an object too... heard your environment, it’s a good way to be present. That’s where life is happening, right now. Is the only thing you have and we have. Future doesn’t exists. Time is like an illusion. Okay that’s it. Hope this helps you and others too...
